Types of Computer Networks
Today I learned about how devices talk to each other on a network.
I spent the day shadowing the network operations team to understand how the company structures its connectivity.
I saw firsthand how the office's internal Local Area Network (LAN) is segmented for different departments.
My mentor then explained how their branch offices are connected via a Wide Area Network (WAN) using secure VPN tunnels. 
Seeing the sheer scale of an enterprise network helped clarify why careful network segmentation is critical for both performance and security.
